      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING TYRA (4) wasn't far away at the finish when 4th and beaten only 5 lengths (30.68) at The Meadows. Returns to favourable track. Has a very good strike-rate from this draw, with three wins from four starts. Rates on top in this line up. AMRON TOMMY (6) was well supported last time and gave a sight after a fast early split but could manage only the minor money, finishing a 2 length third (26.24) over 460m at Warragul. Hard to beat again. KADE (1) turned spotting a big start finishing fourth (17.13) last time in a Grade 5 at Murray Bridge Straight. Form at the trip sound including five wins. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Great chance to atone. SWEET NUGGET (2) is another with top-three prospects.",
